<title>UK: HSBC slides after Far East sell-off.</title>
<headline>HSBC slides after Far East sell-off.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-12-06</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in HSBC Holdings were sharply lower on Friday, tracking heavy losses in the Far East markets overnight.</p>
<p>The shares were 38p lower at 12.85-1/2 stg by 0853 GMT.</p>
<p>In Hong Kong the Hang Seng index fell 2.88 percent or 388 points as remarks made by Fed chairman Alan Greenspan sparked renewed interest rate jitters and a sell-off in U.S bonds.</p>
<p>In Tokyo, the Nikkei 225 fell 3.19 percent, losing 667.20 points.</p>
<p>--London Newsroom +44 171 542 4027</p>
